-sS: TCP SYN scan (stealth scan).
-sT: TCP connect scan.
-sU: UDP scan.
-sA: TCP ACK scan.
-sX: TCP Xmas scan.
-sN: TCP Null scan.
-sI: Idle scan.


-sV: Service version detection.
-sC: Run default scripts (useful for service enumeration).
-A: Enable OS detection, version detection, script scanning, and traceroute.
--script=

-sn: Host discovery only (ping scan, no port scan).
-Pn: Treat all hosts as up, no ping scan.

TLS/SSL Related
--script ssl-enum-ciphers: List supported SSL/TLS cipher suites.
--script ssl-cert: Get the SSL certificate information.
